<paragraph id="2670974A46AA8110D00E6C028F6479E5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA34F4AC81EDCCEA8BCCF403BEFB56BE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Endemic to Jamaica where it appears to be common in thickets, scrub and in forest relics on limestone hills.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A0703F8A468FC8FE35CE18FE90D2002" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
